Outside in the savanna it is hard for a primates with a digestive system such as human to meet their need for amino acid from available plant sources.
It also it has serious consequences if you refrain: growth depression, malnutrition and ultimately death.
The most readily available plant resources would have been the proteins in leaves and legumes, but these are difficult to digest for primates like us, unless they are cooked.
In contrast, animal food sources (antes, termites, eggs) are not only easily digested, but also provide large amounts of proteins, all of which contain essential amino acids.
