The official currency of the Falkland Islands is the Falkland Islands Pound (FKP), whose value is determined in accordance with the value of the British Pound (GBP).
Money can be exchanged in the only bank on the island located in Stanley opposite the FIC West Store.
The British pound is generally accepted everywhere on the islands and on Stanley credit cards. The US dollar is also often accepted.
On the remote islands credit cards are probably not likely to be accepted, however, but UK and US currency can be accepted; ask owners in advance what payment method is accepted.
